|------|--------|-----------|-----------------|

Traceability:
Notes:
```

---

## Excel-Friendly Output

When the user asks for Excel, spreadsheet, CSV, regression suite, or table format, use this structure:

| Test Case ID | Suite | Scenario | Title | Description | Preconditions | Step No. | Action | Test Data | Expected Result | Priority | Severity | Behavior | Type | Layer | Automation | Status | Traceability |
|--------------|-------|----------|-------|-------------|---------------|----------|--------|-----------|-----------------|----------|----------|----------|------|-------|------------|--------|--------------|

Rules:

- One row per step.
- Repeat test case metadata for every row.
- Use `TC-001`, `TC-002`, etc.
- Keep actions atomic.
- Keep expected results observable.
- Use line breaks only when necessary.
- Do not merge cells in plain markdown output.

---

## Compact Scenario Matrix

When the user asks for high-level scenarios only, use:

| Scenario ID | Area | Scenario | Positive/Negative/Edge | Priority | Risk | Notes |
|-------------|------|----------|------------------------|----------|------|-------|

