# Feature-Specific Coverage Patterns

## CRUD Features

For every Create, Read, Update, and Delete feature, cover:

- successful create
- required field validation
- duplicate handling
- successful details display
- successful update
- partial update
- cancel edit
- delete confirmation
- delete cancellation
- deleted record no longer appears
- permissions for each operation
- audit/logging if applicable
- database verification if applicable

---

## Search and Filter Features

Cover:

- exact match
- partial match
- no results
- multiple filters combined using AND
- multi-select filter using OR within same field
- clear/reset filters
- filter persistence after pagination
- filter persistence after refresh if required
- special characters
- case sensitivity if applicable
- performance with large result set

---

## Pagination and Sorting

Cover:

- first page
- next page
- previous page
- last page
- page size change
- disabled previous on first page
- disabled next on last page
- sorting ascending
- sorting descending
- sorting with filters applied
- sorting with duplicate values
- no duplicate or missing records across pages

---

## Forms

Cover:

- all required fields
- optional fields blank
- minimum length
- maximum length
- one above maximum
- valid special characters
- invalid special characters
- save enabled/disabled state
- validation timing
- cancel behavior
- unsaved changes behavior
- refresh during edit
- browser back during edit

---

## File Upload

Cover:

- valid file type
- invalid file type
- max file size
- over max file size
- empty file
- duplicate file
- corrupted file
- upload cancellation
- upload timeout
- virus scan failure if applicable
- preview/download behavior

---

## API Features

Cover:

- 200/201 success
- 400 validation error
- 401 unauthenticated
- 403 unauthorized
- 404 not found
- 409 conflict
- 422 business validation
- 429 rate limit if applicable
- 500 server error handling
- idempotency
- duplicate request
- schema validation
- invalid data type
- missing required field
- boundary values
- response time
- database side effects

---

## Database Validation

When DB access is relevant, include validation points for:

- insert
- update
- delete/soft delete
- status changes
- timestamps
- created_by / updated_by
- audit trail
- relation integrity
- computed fields
- rollback behavior
- duplicate prevention

Do not invent table or column names. Use placeholders or repository-discovered names.

---

## Security

Cover when applicable:

- unauthenticated access
- unauthorized role access
- IDOR
- SQL injection
- XSS
- CSRF-sensitive actions
- sensitive data exposure
- token/session expiration
- permission escalation
- direct URL access

---

## Accessibility

Cover when applicable:

- keyboard navigation
- focus order
- visible focus indicator
- screen reader labels
- error message association
- color contrast
- modal focus trap
- accessible table headers
- accessible form labels

---

# Quality Checklist Before Finalizing

Before returning test cases, verify:

- Every test case has a clear title.
- Every title follows `Verify [outcome] when [condition]`.
- Every case has preconditions.
- Every case has atomic steps.
- Every step has an observable expected result.
- Test data is explicit and safe.
- Positive, negative, and edge cases are included.
- Smoke tests are included.
- Priority and severity are assigned.
- Behavior is Positive or Negative.
- Suite hierarchy is consistent.
- Test cases are independent.
- Requirement traceability is included when possible.
- No real credentials or production data are included.
- Count meets minimum target for the feature type.
- Missing assumptions are documented.

